Shiva is the third diety of Hindu triad of great gods, others being Brahma and Vishnu. Shiva is often referred to as the Destroyer, but it might be better to think of him as God of Transformation, since he is often associated with creation which comes out of destruction.

Dhoop's are another masala sub-group. They are an extruded incense, lacking a core bamboo stick. Many dhoop's have very concentrated scents and put out a lot of smoke when burned.
